cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with point set upsampling, which is a problem in computer graphics and computer vision. The use of deep neural networks and architectural design contributions suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The focus on training a cascade of patch-based upsampling networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
